[Linked List Cycle](https://leetcode.com/problems/linked-list-cycle/)

```{=tex}
\begin{gather}
\forall a, b, m \in \mathbb{Z}^+, \exists n \text{ such that } a \equiv b + n \pmod{m} \text{ and } 0 \leq y < m.\\
\therefore a + n \equiv b + 2n \pmod{m}.
\end{gather}
```
